    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.97/211a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Food Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d473fn1">Transmitted by the Secretary of State,
                        No. 7836.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-20T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Will you kindly inform <persName corresp="#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>,
                        <persName>Durand</persName>, <persName>Simms</persName> and others
                    interested that do not believe any conclusive program of next year’s food
                    supplies to Allies can be arrived at before the middle of July when all our
                    crops are defined and our animal resources recounted. In this view I propose to
                    come myself to Europe with technical staff to consider the whole situation with
                    our European food colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_HHC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
